{
  "texts": [
    "First, a joint optimization method that combines self-attention fine-tuning via low-rank adaptation (LoRA) [18] with layer normalization [19] is proposed to enhance the understanding of clinical images by a general visual encoder.",
    "The training target is the text generation loss of the large language model (LLM) without introducing extra clinical image-text pairs for further pretraining.",
    "Second, the joint fine-tuning process for both the image-text transformation layer and the multilayer perceptron (MLP) layer of the language model is designed to allow the LLM to draw upon its internal capability to generate the final report.",
    "In addition, we further incorporate the prior information to light the specialized clinical knowledge inherent in the LLM.",
    "Also, the clinical tag and brief description of the image as a text prompt are fed into the model for training and prediction."
  ]
}